I think we should build calling `poll(timeout=0)` into the client.  You can pass in a callback to the produce function that'll get called after the message is delivered, one potential option would be something like this:

```
def produce(message):
    q = queue.Queue(maxsize=1)
    func on_delivery(message, err):
        q.add((message, err))
    kafka.publish(message, on_delivery=on_delivery)
    message, err = flush(q)
    return message, err

def _flush(q):
    kafka.poll(timeout=0)
    while q.empty():
        kafka.poll(timeout=0)
    return q.get(block=False)
```

