There are two places where this is used:

1. Functional.h for a performance improvement if a pybind11 function is detected. On failure, runs slower.

2. cpp_function's sibling feature for function overloading.

Think of the following

module 1:
module_<..> a;
a.attr("foo") = cpp_function([](int a));

module 2:
object a = import(a);
a.attr("bar") = cpp_function([](string a){}, sibling(a.attr("foo"));

The sibling feature means that the "bar" function will call "foo" if the input cannot be cast to string.

