The reason I suggested to have a generic interface (`UniquePricingInfo`) and a special implementation (`LambdaFunctionPricing`) is because you can put lambda specific questions and answers in the implementation where the generic interface can have a generic method which won't expose resource specific stuff to the outside.

Since you created this `UniquePricingInfo`, you can now have an abstract method in that interface;

```
class UniquePricingInfo(ABC):
  
  @abstractmethod
  def ask_questions(self):
    pass
```

And in the `LambdaFunctionPricing` implementation you can implement that method as;

```
class LambdaFunctionPricing(UniquePricingInfo):

  def ask_questions(self):
    # lambda resource specific questions
    self.ask_lambda_function_questions()
    ...
    ...
```

